The paper deals with a secrecy system with side information, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a distortion metric to measure the fidelity of communication suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses achievable rate-distortion regions, which is a common topic in coding theory (cs.CC).
